# Authoritative ground-truth record for this template. The registry generator
# (build_registry.py) copies the block below verbatim into eval/templates/README.md;
# --verify re-runs the query against GraphDB and asserts the live answer still
# equals the `answer` below. Keep it in sync with the query (or let --verify catch you).
#
# --- registry ---
# seeds:
#   - { label: Tamoxifen, uri: db:DB00675 }
#   - { label: breast cancer, uri: do:1612 }
# chain: "Compound --binds--> Gene <--associates-- Disease (ASK — does the path exist?)"
# answer: true
# --- end registry ---
#
# Type 09_path_existence. The committed pair (Tamoxifen, breast cancer) is iconic and
# the answer is TRUE: tamoxifen binds 11 genes that are associated with breast cancer,
# so the metapath exists. The query is an ASK over the property path
# `binds / ^associates` (compound binds a gene; that gene is, inversely, associated
# with the disease). The graph can also name the bridging gene(s) for provenance (H6).
# The producer (step 3) rewrites both VALUES with each sampled pair and must include
# false cases (no shared gene) for the boolean to carry signal. Order is irrelevant
# here — the path is symmetric in existence — but the roles (compound vs disease) are
# fixed by node type.

PREFIX db: <https://identifiers.org/drugbank/>
PREFIX do: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/DOID_>
PREFIX hetio: <https://het.io/schema/>

ASK {
  VALUES ?compound { db:DB00675 }     # Tamoxifen — producer rewrites this line
  VALUES ?disease  { do:1612 }        # breast cancer — producer rewrites this line
  ?compound hetio:binds / ^hetio:associates ?disease .
}
